The default value of this property is an expression that evaluates to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"standard"},{"text":". Set this property to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":" to reset it to the default value.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can set this property to an expression containing any of the following:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Constant "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNHillshadeMethod"},{"type":"text","text":" values"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Any of the following constant string values:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"standard"},{"type":"text","text":": The legacy hillshade method."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"basic"},{"type":"text","text":": Basic hillshade. Uses a simple physics model where the reflected"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"light intensity is proportional to the cosine of the angle between the incident"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"light and the surface normal. Similar to GDAL’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gdaldem"},{"type":"text","text":" default algorithm."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"combined"},{"type":"text","text":": Hillshade algorithm whose intensity scales with slope. Similar"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to GDAL’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gdaldem"},{"type":"text","text":" with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"-combined"},{"type":"text","text":" option."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"igor"},{"type":"text","text":": Hillshade algorithm which tries to minimize effects on other map"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"features beneath. Similar to GDAL’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gdaldem"},{"type":"text","text":" with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"-igor"},{"type":"text","text":" option."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"multidirectional"},{"type":"text","text":": Hillshade with multiple illumination directions. Uses"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the basic hillshade model with multiple independent light sources."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Predefined functions, including mathematical and string operators"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Conditional expressions"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Variable assignments and references to assigned variables"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Step functions applied to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"$zoomLevel"},{"type":"text","text":" variable"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This property does not support applying interpolation functions to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"$zoomLevel"},{"type":"text","text":" variable or applying interpolation or step functions to feature"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"attributes."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNHillshadeStyleLayer":{"role":"symbol","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNHillshadeStyleLayer","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is a style layer that renders raster "},{"type":"text","text":"digital elevation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"model"},{"type":"text","text":" (DEM) tiles on the map."}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnhillshadestylelayer","title":"MLNHillshadeStyleLayer","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNHillshadeStyleLayer"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNHillshadeStyleLayer","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNHillshadeStyle